==English==

===Adjective===
'''vicarious'''

# Experienced or gained through someone else.
#: ''I got a certain vicarious pleasure from watching them win.''
# Done on behalf of others
#: ''The concept of vicarious atonement, that one person can atone for the sins of another, is found in many religions.''
# "Vicariously I live while the whole world dies"
#: ''(Tool, 10 000 Days, Vicarious) The term 'vicariously is of ambiguous authenticity.''